## Things that are true across all archetypes

### Texture is in our DNA
Every post should have at least one of these textural elements somewhere:
- A **soft grain/noise** overlay on solid color fields (subtle — don't overdo)
- **Halftone dot circles** (a circle filled with a dot pattern, in moss or sand)
- **Hollow rings** (1.5–3px stroke, anchored to an edge or floating)
- **Solid filled circles** in pebble or moss

Combinations of these are great — a halftone dot circle overlapping a solid pebble circle is on-brand. They live in the negative space, never on top of the words.

### Color anchors
Most posts use **Mossy Green** or **Pebble White** as the ground. Sand and Moss-Mid are common accents. We rarely use full saturation except for the sub-brand colors (KIDS Aqua, YTH Punch Yellow). Photos lean cool/neutral, not warm.

### Type behavior
- **Quotes & scripture**: Recoleta Italic is used often for the quote body. Recoleta Regular for headlines.
- **Reference / metadata** (book + verse, date, sermon series name): smaller, sometimes Recoleta Bold
- **Body / supporting**: Helvetica Neue Light or Regular
- **Lowercase by default**, but proper-noun event titles ("Financial Peace University") and scripture references ("Lamentations 3:22-23") use title case.

### Casing rule (strict)
**Lowercase everything by default.** The only exceptions are biblical words and references to them:
- **Always capitalized**: God, Jesus, Lord, Father, Son, Holy Spirit, Christ, Savior, Word (when meaning Scripture)
- **Always capitalized when referring to God**: He, His, Him, You, Your (in prayer/address)
- **Always capitalized**: books of the Bible and scripture references — "Lamentations 3:22-23", "Mark 1:35"

Everything else is lowercase. That includes:
- Pastor names and attribution: "— pastor ricky", "— pastor severin awori lwali"
- Event and program titles: "financial peace university", "21 days of prayer"
- Sermon series names
- Days, months, locations
- Roles (pastor, elder, leader)

This applies across **all** archetypes — including the editorial sermon pull-quote. If a previous archetype file shows Title Case in an attribution, treat this rule as overriding it.

### Anatomy across all archetypes
1. **Ground** — color, photo, or photo-with-overlay
2. **Texture layer** — grain, halftone, rings, or solid circles
3. **Headline / quote** — the main idea
4. **Reference / attribution** — who said it, where it's from, when it's happening
5. **Brand mark** — symbol, wordmark, or sub-brand lockup (sometimes implicit, e.g. on Stonecreek-only posts)

### Don'ts
- No emoji
- No drop shadows on type
- No gradients as primary backgrounds
- No warm/orange filters on photos
- No solid rectangles behind type to make it readable — pick a different photo or move the type instead
- No more than two textural elements layered (it gets noisy)
- No filling the whole canvas with type — give it air

---

## When in doubt

- **Is the content reverent / weighty?** Lean Mossy Green ground, Recoleta italic, more space.
- **Is it inviting / community-focused?** Pebble or Sand ground, photo-forward, room for warmth.
- **Is it KIDS?** Aqua + Sunny Glow palette, more energetic shapes.
- **Is it YTH?** Black ground, Punch Yellow accents, big and confident.

If the content doesn't clearly fit one of the six archetypes, ask before designing.
